Among the 1452 patients tested, 777 patients (777/1452, 54%) were positive for at least one respiratory virus. Fifty-nine cases of RSV infection were detected in total (4% (59/1452) of patients with ILI, 8% (59/777) of patients with at least one respiratory virus), 21 in 2012/13, 13 in 2013/14 and 25 in 2014/15 (Table 1
, Fig. 2
).
